race.comment: LAND OF FIRE (6) kept coming only to just miss when fresh from a spell last start over 1100m at Toodyay. Sure to derive great benefit from that run. Can sit a touch closer today back in grade slightly and he looks the one to beat on the back of that performance. TEABISCUIT (1) got the prize two runs ago at Moora. Couldn't follow that up last time out when tenth over 1100m at Ascot, beaten 3.5 lengths. Right back in grade today following a dominant win in a similar race at Moora two back. Nicely placed to return to winning ways. ANGEL'S MY NAME (7) finished ninth over 1500m at Bunbury All Weather at her most recent appearance on July 3. Has found a suitable race and is worth including. GET OUT MICK (3) gave away a considerable start over 1190m at Moora last time before hitting the line well to finish fourth. Solid top-three prospects. STAR POWER (5) has claims off a good effort last time out.
